FBIS3-25311 "drafr031_c_94020" FBIS-AFR-94-031 Document Type:Daily Report 15 Feb 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Defense Force Considering Strengthening Border Security MB1002073494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 0500 GMT 10 Feb 94 MB1002073494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The Defense Force is considering tougher steps to halt the deteriorating situation along the South African border with Mozambique and Swaziland. Major General Reg Otto of Eastern Transvaal Command said the activities of armed smugglers, stock thieves, and people who cross the border illegally might compel the Defense Force to switch the electrified border fence from alarm to deadly strength. Gen. Otto said the security situation was becoming a burden on local infrastructure and agriculture.
